  "decision_conditions": [
    "REASON: The proposed roof extension by reason of its excessive design, scale and massing would represent an overdominant and unsightly interruption to the unaltered and uniform roof forms along this section of the terrace along Liverpool Road. The development would be readily visible from the public realm and is considered to have a significant detrimental impact on the visual appearance of this prominent corner building diminishing the existing significance of the host building and wider terrace to which it forms part. The proposal is contrary to policies D1 (Overall design), D4 (Designing in context), D11 (Alterations and extensions) & D25 ( Roof extensions)  of the Islington Unitary Development Plan 2002, Islington’s Urban Design Guidance 2006, policy  9  of Islington’s Draft Core Strategy, conservation guidance note 10 and PPS 5."
